      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Failure",
      "pos": [
        11989,
        11996
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The first request matches the first rule – the origin domain matches the allowed origins, the method matches the allowed methods, and the header matches the allowed headers – and so succeeds.",
      "pos": [
        11998,
        12189
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The second request does not match the first rule because the method does not match the allowed methods.",
      "pos": [
        12191,
        12294
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It does, however, match the second rule, so it succeeds.",
      "pos": [
        12295,
        12351
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The third request matches the second rule in its origin domain and method, so no further rules are evaluated.",
      "pos": [
        12353,
        12462
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>x-ms-client-request-id header<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> is not allowed by the second rule, so the request fails, despite the fact that the semantics of the third rule would have allowed it to succeed.",
      "pos": [
        12463,
        12652
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        12655,
        12824
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Although this example shows a less restrictive rule before a more restrictive one, in general the best practice is to list the most restrictive rules first."
    },
    {
      "content": "Understanding how the Vary header is set",
      "pos": [
        12829,
        12869
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Vary<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> header is a standard HTTP/1.1 header consisting of a set of request header fields that advise the browser or user agent about the criteria that were selected by the server to process the request.",
      "pos": [
        12871,
        13077
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Vary<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> header is mainly used for caching by proxies, browsers, and CDNs, which use it to determine how the response should be cached.",
      "pos": [
        13078,
        13215
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For details, see the specification for the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Vary header<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        13216,
        13329
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When the browser or another user agent caches the response from a CORS request, the origin domain is cached as the allowed origin.",
      "pos": [
        13331,
        13461
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When a second domain issues the same request for a storage resource while the cache is active, the user agent retrieves the cached origin domain.",
      "pos": [
        13462,
        13607
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The second domain does not match the cached domain, so the request fails when it would otherwise succeed.",
      "pos": [
        13608,
        13713
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In certain cases, Azure Storage sets the Vary header to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Origin<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to instruct the user agent to send the subsequent CORS request to the service when the requesting domain differs from the cached origin.",
      "pos": [
        13714,
        13917
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13919,
        14022
      ],
      "content": "Azure Storage sets the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Vary<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> header to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Origin<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> for actual GET/HEAD requests in the following cases:"
    },
    {
      "content": "When the request origin exactly matches the allowed origin defined by a CORS rule.",
      "pos": [
        14026,
        14108
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To be an exact match, the CORS rule may not include a wildcard ' * ' character.",
      "pos": [
        14109,
        14188
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is no rule matching the request origin, but CORS is enabled for the storage service.",
